issue(id="0007" status="closed")
  title Automate the scrubs validation plan with canonical local probes
  user-story
    as-a scrubs maintainer changing bootstrap, auth, or dirty-boundary behavior
    i-want the documented validation plan encoded as repeatable scripts
    so-that regression checks can be run locally and on suitable runners without relying on memory or one-off terminal transcripts
  premise.
    Scrubs now ships a canonical local-first validation runner in
    `vms/validate.nu`, exposed through `just scrubs-validate`, plus a
    lightweight hosted-CI-safe parse check in `just scrubs-validation-static`.
    The runner encodes the documented baseline directly: bootstrap a fresh
    disposable guest, confirm repeat-bootstrap survivability, confirm
    clean-space `gh` and Codex auth work without login ceremony, confirm the
    dirty boundary still hides clean auth surfaces, and confirm HTTPS Git
    still works through the scrubs-owned `gh` helper path.

    The product constraint remains explicit. GitHub-hosted macOS arm64 runners
    still cannot exercise the real Apple Silicon `vz` path, so the full
    validation story stays local or self-hosted. Hosted CI only verifies the
    static command surface instead of pretending to run the real guest flow.

    The final design is now settled. The main artifact is a reusable runner
    command rather than a prose-only checklist, while `try-*` guests remain
    supplemental module fixtures that can be passed in as shims for targeted
    coverage rather than replacing the default baseline harness.

    Validation completed on June 11, 2026. Disposable guests
    `scrubs-validate-base-20260611`,
    `scrubs-validate-try-docker-20260611`, and
    `scrubs-validate-try-postgres-20260611` each completed the full scripted
    pass, including repeat bootstrap, clean auth smoke, dirty-boundary smoke,
    HTTPS Git helper probes, and Codex continuity checks. Along the way, the
    runner was tightened to trust its guest-local `.mise.toml` fixture before
    tool installation and to stop running disposable guests before
    `recreate=true` deletion.
  acceptance-criteria
    criterion Scrubs has one or more canonical scripts or commands that encode the documented validation baseline rather than leaving it as README-only operator prose.
    criterion The scripted plan covers repeat bootstrap survivability, clean-space auth smoke, dirty-space visibility smoke, and the HTTPS Git helper path.
    criterion The scripted plan is documented with clear assumptions about required host secrets, disposable guest names, and which checks are expected to be non-destructive.
    criterion The work explicitly distinguishes checks that can run on ordinary GitHub-hosted CI from checks that require local or self-hosted Apple Silicon `vz` capacity.
    criterion At least one maintainer-oriented path can run the scripted validation plan locally end to end and produce an understandable pass/fail result.
    criterion The validation design explains the role of `try-*` guests, including whether they remain as canonical fixtures for module-level smoke coverage or are superseded by a more formal test harness.
  review-items
    item(status="covered").
      The canonical artifact is now a small command suite centered on the
      reusable `vms/validate.nu` runner and the maintainer-facing
      `just scrubs-validate` wrapper, plus the CI-safe
      `just scrubs-validation-static` parse check.
    item(status="covered").
      The baseline intentionally stays focused on bootstrap survivability,
      clean auth, dirty-boundary checks, HTTPS Git helper behavior, and Codex
      continuity. Broader guest-project happy-path tool smokes remain
      supplemental workload coverage rather than part of the default gate, and
      `try-*` shims stay available when a module composition needs that extra
      targeted coverage.
    item(status="covered").
      Host-secret-dependent coverage is now explicit: the canonical runner is
      live-secret-only and fails fast when sealed `gh` or Codex artifacts are
      absent, because dummy-secret coverage would not validate the real clean
      wrappers or Git helper path.
    item(status="covered").
      The GitHub Actions split is now explicit. Hosted CI runs only the static
      validation-surface check, while full guest validation remains local or
      self-hosted on Apple Silicon `vz` capacity.
